description.narrative: Continued capacity strengthening of 750 professionals and para professionals in the social welfare, justice and education systems on child-friendly justice systems, prevention of sexual abuse and exploitation, and referral pathways led to better prevention and multisectoral response for 2,076 children (1,560 girl victims/witnesses of sexual violence and 516 children in conflict with the law). At least 5,963 adolescents and community members benefited from community dialogues on SGBV and the SGBV referral pathway; and multisectoral responses were provided to 2,076 victims/survivors of violence or SGBV (all girls) and 516 children in conflict with the law (42 girls and 474 boys). | Status:Met | As-of Date:31/12/2019
